---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import marketing from "../data/site-data.json";

const { privacy } = marketing.site.pages;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={marketing.site.meta.privacy.title}
  description={marketing.site.meta.privacy.description}
  canonical={marketing.site.meta.privacy.canonical}
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <p class="font-semibold text-slate-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-semibold text-base-content text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-base-content/60">Effective date: February 17, 2026</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base-content/70">
        This Privacy Policy explains how Erudika Ltd. ("Erudika", "we", "us") collects, uses, and protects
        personal data when you visit erudika.com or contact us. We are committed to complying with the GDPR
        and applicable privacy laws.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 mt-8 text-sm text-base-content/70">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">1. Data Controller</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Erudika Ltd., 4 Lelinska chuka Street, Sofia 1618, Bulgaria.
            Email: <a class="text-sky-700" href="mailto:contact@erudika.com">contact@erudika.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-1 mt-2 pl-5 list-disc">
            <li>Contact details you provide (name, email, company, message).</li>
            <li>Account or contract details when you request support or services.</li>
            <li>Technical data such as IP address, browser type, and basic device information.</li>
            <li>Usage data from analytics (pages visited, time on site, referral source).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">3. Legal Bases for Processing</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-1 mt-2 pl-5 list-disc">
            <li>Consent (e.g., marketing emails, optional analytics).</li>
            <li>Contract performance (e.g., providing support or services you request).</li>
            <li>Legitimate interests (e.g., securing our site, improving our services).</li>
            <li>Legal obligations (e.g., accounting and compliance requirements).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-1 mt-2 pl-5 list-disc">
            <li>Respond to inquiries and provide support.</li>
            <li>Deliver products or services you request.</li>
            <li>Improve our website and user experience.</li>
            <li>Maintain security, prevent fraud, and comply with legal obligations.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">5. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We use essential cookies for site functionality. We may use privacy-friendly analytics to
            understand site usage. Where required, we ask for consent before placing non-essential cookies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">6. Sharing and International Transfers</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We share data only with service providers who process data on our behalf (e.g., hosting, email,
            analytics). If data is transferred outside the EEA, we use appropriate safeguards such as
            Standard Contractual Clauses.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We retain personal data only as long as needed for the purposes described, or as required by law.
            We periodically review and delete data that is no longer necessary.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">8. Your Rights</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-1 mt-2 pl-5 list-disc">
            <li>Access your personal data and request a copy.</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to legal requirements).</li>
            <li>Object to processing or request restriction.</li>
            <li>Data portability where applicable.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent.</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">9. Security</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against
            unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Our services are not directed to children under 16, and we do not knowingly collect data from
            children. If you believe a child has provided us data, please contact us.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version on this
            page and update the effective date above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-base-content text-lg">12. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            For privacy-related requests, contact us at
            <a class="text-sky-700" href="mailto:contact@erudika.com">contact@erudika.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
